^["stream"]{
 >>[2026-04-10 13:55] observe — The current image prototype already exists, but it is effect-first: random hover choice, broad selectors, no stable visitation memory, and no semantic mapping between realization and treatment.
 >>[2026-04-10 13:57] observe — Shared hot files from parallel work are already dirty; the cleanest path is to refine `spw-image-metaphysics.js` and `spw-metaphysical-paper.css`, then opt a few existing surfaces into the system rather than widening `style.css`.
 >>[2026-04-10 13:59] decide — Holding an image should be the primary visit ritual. Click remains available to the helper operator, but press-and-hold better matches “mark and return” than a casual click toggle.
 >>[2026-04-10 14:00] taste — The rewarding glow should feel archival and earned, like a remembered folio edge, not like a gamified neon badge.
 >>[2026-04-10 14:16] implement — Replaced the randomized image runtime with semantic treatment mapping, stable image/SVG keying, localStorage-backed visited memory, a compact helper chip, and hold-to-visit gesture handling.
 >>[2026-04-10 14:18] implement — Wired the compression study, scheduler study, and lore.land poster/token into explicit image metadata so the helper surface reads route intent instead of guessing from hover alone.
 >>[2026-04-10 14:20] verify — `node --check public/js/spw-image-metaphysics.js`, direct ESM import of the module, and `git diff --check` all pass. Remaining dirty files in the tree are from adjacent work and were left alone.
}

